<TITLE> Mirza Golam Hafiz's son joins AL </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Nov 3 (bdnews24.com)  The son of late Mirza Golam Hafiz, one of the founders of BNP, joined Awami League on Monday. Mirza Golam Erfan Babu met acting AL president Zillur Rahman at the latter's Gulshan house and joined the party. "I have joined Awami League inspired by the ideals of Bangabandhu (Sheikh Mujibur Rahman)," Babu said. His father was elected from Panchagarh-1 constituency in 1991 general election and later became law minister. bd
